body:
@llorllale In general, 5 to 10; 10 is exceptional, however. 

In ZC's model, I would say as little as possible; I would accept even 1 line of code changed if it moves the project forward. 30min/task is very little any way you look at it. So, the smaller and faster the PR, the better.  Value and speed are key, not code quantity.

In this model, there is one more reason why I don't accept big PRs (5+ files, usually): because they clearly worked more than 30min and it's not ok for the project to accept that.
